= FFII advertisement in Parliamentary Magazine =
->
[ [:PrmatEn: PR Materials]
| [:Parlmag050704En: Parlmag 05-07-04]
| [:SwpatcninoEn: Patent News]
]
----

''An full-page advertisement, designed by Peter Gerwinski, incorporating a new caricature, was published by Parliamentary Magazine 2 days before the software patent directive vote.  It was FFII's 5th advertisement of this kind in the magazine.''

== Outline ==

 * cartoon of a "monopolist" wolf in sheep's coat among "software developper" sheep, all behind a fence titled "software patents", saying "Hey folks, this fence serves us all!"
 * testimonies of [http://www.economic-majority.com/testimony/pitcom/ Pitcom] and [http://www.foreststar.net/testimony/foreststar/ Foreststar]
 * a lot of text, with major headlines
   * Who Profits from EPO Software Patents?
   * Please Don't Let This Happen to Europe
   * Please Vote for the Buzek-Rocard Compromise Amendments!
